ENTRY            C3104   20260219   20260518   20260518       C257
SUBENT        C3104001   20260219   20260518   20260518       C257
BIB                 11         39
TITLE      Experimental study of 53Cr via the (d,pgamma) reaction
AUTHOR     (M.Spieker,L.A.Riley,M.Heinze,A.L.Conley,B.Kelly,
           P.D.Cottle,R.Aggarwal,S.Ajayi,L.T.Baby,S.Baker,
           I.Conroy,I.B.D'Amato,J.Esparza,S.Genty,I.Hay,
           K.W.Kemper,M.I.Khawaja,P.S.Kielb,A.N.Kuchera,
           E.Lopez-Saavedra,A.B.Morelock,J.Piekarewicz,
           A.Sandrik,V.Sitaraman,E.Temanson,C.Wibisono,
           I.Wiedenhoever)
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,112,064331,2025)
           #doi:10.1103/wp85-rthk
INSTITUTE  (1USAFSU,1USAURS,1USADVD)
FACILITY   (VDGT,1USAFSU) 9-MV Super-FN Tandem Van de Graaff
           accelerator at the John D. Fox Superconducting Linear
           Accelerator Laboratory of Florida State University.
DETECTOR   (MAGSP,SCIN) The Super-Enge Split-Pole Spectrograph
            (SE-SPS) and CeBr3 Array (CeBrA) demonstrator, which
           consisted of four 2x2 inch CeBr3 detectors and one
           3x4 inch CeBr3 detector placed around the scattering
           chamber.
SAMPLE     A natural chromium foil of areal density rho = 300
           microg/cm2 evaporated onto a natural 20-microg/cm2
           carbon backing.
METHOD     (COINC) Particle-gamma coincidences between the SE-
           SPS and CeBrA detectors. Two magnetic field settings
           were used, 8.3 and 7.5 kG, to identify excited states
           of 53Cr populated in the 52Cr(d,p) reaction up to
           the neutron-separation energy, Sn=7937.12(14) keV,
           with the position-sensitive focal plane detector of the
            SE-SPS.
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-S) Stated uncertainties for the cross sections
           are statistical uncertainties at the 1-sigma level,
           if you want to add that. For states, where "average"
           was given (unweighted average of the cross section
           obtained at two different field settings) , the
           uncertainty of that cross section corresponds to the
           standard deviation determined from the two
           cross-section values.
STATUS     (APRVD) Approved by M.Spieker on March 9, 2026.
HISTORY    (20260219C) BP
ENDBIB              39
COMMON               1          3
EN
MEV
       16.0
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           46
SUBENT        C3104002   20260219   20260518   20260518       C257
